<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--WeddingHitch     04-04 0112</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Wedding Hitch,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rice Banned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wedding bells are OK, but those who get
married in the Oklahoma County Courthouse can no longer celebrate
with rice or birdseed.
   Oklahoma County Commissioners on Monday voted to ban the
throwing of rice, bird seed, confetti and other similar substances
in and around the courthouse.
   Rice and bird seed traditionally have been tossed at weddings as
symbols of fertility, but the commissioners' action apparently was
not an effort to limit population growth.
   Commissioner F.G. ``Buck'' Buchanan said the policy was enacted
as a safety measure.
   ``We've had people who have been hurt by sliding on rice and so
forth,'' he said.
</TEXT>
