<SECOND>PM-Germany-Ship Fire,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tour Ship Catches Fire on Rhine; Six People Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESEL, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A French tour ship with 42 aboard
people caught fire on the Rhine River today, badly damaging the
vessel and injuring six passengers, officials said.
   Police and fire boats rescued all 34 passengers and eight crew
members from the burning Alsace 1, said Klaus van Beeck of the
North Rhine-Westphalia state Water Protection Police.
   ``Two people were hospitalized because of shock and four because
of smoke inhalation,'' van Beeck said by telephone from his office
in Wesel, about 25 east of the Dutch border.
   The Alsace 1 was near Wesel when the fire broke out. Two fire
boats fought the blaze, but police said the ship sustained major
damage.
   ``I don't know the exact amount of damage on board the boat, but
it was considerable,'' said van Beeck. He said the cause of the
fire was under investigation.
   According to van Beeck, the Alsace 1 is owned by the Alsace
Croizierez firm of Strasbourg.
   On Monday, a tanker loaded with fuel oil ran aground near
Oppenheim and spilled a small amount of its cargo into the Rhine.
