<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--FlightProblem     04-04 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Flight Problem,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Engine Trouble Forces Paris Flight Back To Airport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Pan Am jet bound for Paris returned to Miami
after an engine shut down about 10 minutes into the flight, airline
officials said today.
   The engine shutdown occurred Monday night on Flight 134 to Paris
and Frankfurt, said Susan Timper, a Pan Am spokeswoman. She said
the shutdown never posed a great risk, and ``there was no fire in
the engine.''
   The 412 passengers aboard the Boeing 747 were put on another
flight and redeparted for Paris at 2:19 a.m. today, she said.
   ``Once the passengers came back, we gave them some meal vouchers
and we took care of them the best we could,'' Ms. Timper said.
``Naturally there might have been some unfavorable passenger
reaction, but the shutdown was routine, there was never any danger
in flight and the plane landed without incident.''
   She said most passengers took the inconvenience well.
</TEXT>
