<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Soviet-Bibles     04-04 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Soviet-Bibles,0144</SECOND>
<HEAD>Swedes Shipping Bibles to Soviet Union</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An evangelical organization will send
12 million Bibles to the Soviet Union by 1995, a newspaper reported
Tuesday.
   Until last year, Bibles were carried individually into the
Soviet Union, according to Josef Oestby, chairman of the Swedish
organization known as Bibles to All.
   ``But it's a different situation now,'' Oestby told the Dagen
newspaper. ``When we were in Moscow for negotiations ... no
obstacles whatsoever were raised by Soviet authorities.''
   The Bibles, in Russian and Ukranian, will be distributed by the
Soviet Ministry for Religion, he said.
   The program, which will cost $13 million, will be funded by
members of Swedish evangelical congregations, Oestby said.
   In November, Nordic Bible Societies began sending 150,000
scriptures in approved truck convoys across the Finnish border, he
said.
