<HEAD>Tour Boat Catches Fire on Rhine; Six People Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESEL, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire swept through a French tour
boat carrying 42 people on the Rhine River on Tuesday, injuring six
passengers and damaging the vessel, officials said.
   Police and fire boats rescued the 34 passengers and eight crew
members from the 109-foot Alsace 1, which caught fire near Wesel,
according to Klaus van Beeck, spokesman for local Water Protection
Police.
   Two people were hospitalized for shock and four for smoke
inhalation, van Beeck said.
   Two fire boats fought the blaze, but the vessel sustained
considerable damage, Van Beeck said.
   The cause of the fire was under investigation.
   It was the second major accident on the Rhine River in West
Germany in two days. On Monday, an oil tanker ran aground near
Oppenheim but was later towed to safety and its cargo transferred
to another ship.
</TEXT>
