<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Moore     04-04 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Moore,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Widow Of Sculptor Henry Moore Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Irina Moore, 82, widow of sculptor Henry Moore,
died at her home in Much Hadham near Cambridge on Tuesday, her
attorneys said.
   Attorneys Goodman Derrick and Co. did not disclose the cause of
death.
   Irina Radetzky, a Russian emigre born in Kiev, was an art
student when she met Moore in 1928. They married the following year
and are survived by their only child, Mary, born in 1946, and three
grandchildren.
   Moore was regarded as the greatest living sculptor when he died
at age 88 on Aug. 31, 1986, at the village of Much Hadham, where
the couple had lived since 1948.
   He left instructions that none of his unfinished works should be
completed, except for finishing touches and then only with his
wife's permission.
</TEXT>
