<FIRST>r a AM-LettermanIntruder     04-04 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Letterman Intruder,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Who Says She's Letterman's Wife Ruled Incompetent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORWALK, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who insists she is David
Letterman's wife was ruled incompetent to stand trial Tuesday on
charges of breaking into the talk show host's home.
   Superior Court Judge Harold H. Dean's ruling came after a state
psychiatrist testified that Margaret Ray is unable to assist in her
own defense.
   The judge committed Ray to a mental hospital in Newtown for up
to 18 months. She had been in prison under $5,000 bail since her
arrest in February.
   Ray, 36, is charged with burglary, larceny, criminal trespass
and drug offenses in connection with break-ins at Letterman's New
Canaan home on Feb. 24 and 28.
   Another judge found Ray incompetent in June after she was caught
driving Letterman's Porsche in New York City. Days later she was
found wandering around his home in the exclusive community 40 miles
north of New York City.
   Mark W. Ford, Letterman's attorney, has said Letterman does not
know Ray.
