<DATELINE>VALDEZ, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities have not ruled out criminal
charges against other crewmen on the Exxon Valdez, including the
third mate who was in command when the tanker ran aground, a state
official said Tuesday.
   ``If our investigation finds evidence to support criminal
prosecution of any other person, we will do that,'' said Larry
Weeks, Alaska director of criminal prosecutions.
   Capt. Joseph Hazelwood, who was fired and charged with being
drunk at the time of the accident in Prince William Sound, had left
Gregory T. Cousins of Tampa, Fla., on the bridge even though he was
not certified to be in command in that body of water.
