Exxon does not know where they were at the time of the accident,
said spokeswoman Sharon Curran-Wescott. She would not release their
names.
   ``Obviously we want to know that answer to those questions
because it's clear the operating requirments of Exxon and the
federal government were not followed,'' she said.
