<FIRST>r i AM-Italy-Terrorists     04-04 0135</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Terrorists,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Detain Three After Raid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Tuesday they held three people
for questioning in connection with a cache of arms, explosives and
documents found in a Milan attic.
   Police said the apartment was believed to be the abandoned
hideout of leftist terrorists.
   In the attic police found three pistols, a rifle, a
hand-grenade, three dynamite sticks, ammunition, two
radio-receivers, bullet-proof vests, material for counterfeiting
documents, and documents related to two different terrorist groups
_ the Red Brigades and Organized Communists for Proletarian
Liberation.
   Police said the hideout was probably abandoned in January after
officers arrested eight reputed members of the gang following a
bank holdup.
   The cache was discovered by the apartment owner, who went to the
building because the tenants had not paid rent for months.
</TEXT>
