<TEXT>
   Construction spending was nearly flat in
February as a small increase in government projects was offset by
slower work on housing and other non-government buildings, the
Commerce Department says.
   February's performance was the weakest since construction
spending declined 0.2 percent last August, the department said
Monday. Analysts said rising interest rates and caution about the
economic outlook were holding back building activity.
