<FIRST>r f BC-NCR-SouthAfrica     04-04 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-NCR-South Africa,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>NCR Selling South African Subsidiary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAYTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NCR Corp. announced today it plans to sell
its South African subsidiary and market its products through a
distributor.
   NCR Products in South Africa will be distributed by Fintech
Ltd., which will acquire a controlling interest in the subsidiary.
The balance of the shares will be acquired by European investors.
   Fintech is a subsidiary of Allied Electronics Corp. Ltd., or
Altron, a South African-owned group of technology-based companies.
   The transactions are subject to certain conditions, including
government approval. Terms were not disclosed.
   ``The decision was a difficult one,'' said M.Y. Stephan, vice
president of NCR's Latin America-Middle East-Africa group. ``It was
based on a careful evaluation of the interests of all NCR
shareholders, including the customers and people of NCR in South
Africa.''
   W.P. Venter, Altron chairman, said the company plans to retain
the subsidiary's management and its approximately 500 employees.
   NCR said the impact on revenue or earnings would not be
substantial.
</TEXT>
