<HEAD>Du Pont and Japanese Company Plan Ink Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Du Pont Co. and Toyo Ink Manufacturing
Co. Ltd. of Japan announced plans Tuesday for a joint venture to
market inks to commercial printers in North America.
   Du Pont plans to market inks manufactured at Toyo plants in
Japan through Toyo-Du Pont International Ink.
   ``Toyo offers major competitive strengths with its high-quality
inks and advanced technology,'' said Edward F. Moran, director of
