<FIRST>r f AM-Britain-Reuters     04-04 0129</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Britain-Reuters,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>Katharine Graham to Join Reuter Board of Trustees</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Katharine Graham, chairman and chief executive
officer of Washington Post Co., has been appointed to the board of
Reuter trustees which oversees the independence of the London-based
international news agency, the board announced Tuesday.
   Mrs. Graham and Sir Nicholas Browne-Wilkinson, a senior English
judge, are the two new appointees to the board, replacing Kingman
Brewster, the former Yale University president and U.S. ambassador
to Britain who died in November, and British broadcaster John
Freeman, who has stepped down, said Lord McGregor, chairman of the
trust.
   The 14-member board enforces a code of principles that include
preventing Reuters from passing into the hands of any single owner
or group, and safeguarding its editorial independence and
impartiality.
</TEXT>
