<FIRST>r f BC-Lorenzo     04-04 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Lorenzo,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Texas Air Chief Gets No Excuses Award</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Following in the footsteps of Vice President Dan
Quayle and entertainer LaToya Jackson, Texas Air Corp. Chairman
Frank Lorenzo is the winner of the ``No Excuses Award of the
Month.''
   The award will be announced in the No Excuses Sportswear print
trade ad campaign, which includes a full-page advertisement in
Women's Wear Daily on Wednesday, the company announced.
   Lorenzo, boss of strike-torn Eastern Airlines, will receive a
wardrobe of No Excuses jeans for himself and his family as well as
a bronzed statue of jeans.
   The award, previously won by Quayle and Jackson, is ``dedicated
to the principle that to err is human, but to take the heat and
make no excuses for it is divine,'' the company said.
</TEXT>
